WEBVTT

1
00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:48.480
<i>NARRATOR: "The changing</i>
<i>of the seasons</i>

2
00:00:48.560 --> 00:00:50.520
<i>"brings wonder to the world</i>

3
00:00:50.720 --> 00:00:54.560
<i>"For ages has the magic</i>
<i>of the fairies been unfurled</i>

4
00:00:55.200 --> 00:00:59.600
<i>"But nature's greatest changes</i>
<i>come beneath the autumn sky</i>

5
00:01:00.080 --> 00:01:04.800
<i>"and mysteries reveal themselves</i>
<i>as harvest time draws nigh</i>

6
00:01:05.520 --> 00:01:10.800
<i>"This year, a shimmering blue moon</i>
<i>will rise before the frost</i>

7
00:01:11.400 --> 00:01:16.400
<i>"Perhaps its rays can light the way</i>
<i>to find what has been lost"</i>

8
00:01:31.480 --> 00:01:35.760
(SINGING)<i> Time to turn the maple</i>
<i>brilliant crimson</i>

9
00:01:36.240 --> 00:01:41.040
<i>Time to turn the Aspen</i>
<i>sparkling gold</i>

10
00:01:41.120 --> 00:01:45.320
<i>Time to tumble apples</i>
<i>from their branches</i>

11
00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:49.480
<i>Time to tell</i>
<i>the breezes crisp and cold</i>

12
00:01:49.600 --> 00:01:53.080
<i>A chilling</i>

13
00:01:53.160 --> 00:01:59.800
<i>Folds the countryside</i>

14
00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:06.840
<i>Kiss of morning mist</i>
<i>upon the meadow</i>

15
00:02:07.440 --> 00:02:12.080
<i>Scent of wood smoke</i>
<i>swirling in the air</i>

16
00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:16.480
<i>Signals that it's high time</i>
<i>for the harvest</i>

17
00:02:17.080 --> 00:02:20.720
<i>Every pumpkin, peach</i>
<i>and prickly pear</i>

18
00:02:20.800 --> 00:02:27.680
<i>With ripened fruit to bear</i>

19
00:02:27.880 --> 00:02:30.640
<i>If you believe</i>

20
00:02:30.720 --> 00:02:32.800
<i>In who you are</i>

21
00:02:33.200 --> 00:02:37.200
<i>Who you were</i>
<i>always meant to be</i>

22
00:02:38.120 --> 00:02:42.760
<i>If you open up your heart</i>

23
00:02:42.920 --> 00:02:46.760
<i>Then you set your spirit free</i>

24
00:02:47.760 --> 00:02:52.520
<i>In this time of the season</i>

25
00:02:52.600 --> 00:02:56.840
<i>Every leaf on every tree</i>

26
00:02:56.920 --> 00:02:59.520
<i>Will start to shine</i>

27
00:02:59.680 --> 00:03:01.680
<i>Come and see</i>

28
00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:04.240
<i>Take my hand</i>

29
00:03:04.480 --> 00:03:06.560
<i>Come with me</i>

30
00:03:06.640 --> 00:03:11.840
<i>And fly</i>

31
00:03:14.960 --> 00:03:16.320
(GOOSE HONKING)

32
00:03:17.680 --> 00:03:18.960
Oh! Oh!

33
00:03:20.960 --> 00:03:22.960
Yeah, okay. There you go!

34
00:03:23.240 --> 00:03:24.640
No, no, no!

35
00:03:30.320 --> 00:03:31.600
Good job.

36
00:03:35.800 --> 00:03:40.040
<i>In this time of the season</i>

37
00:03:40.600 --> 00:03:44.760
<i>Every leaf on every tree</i>

38
00:03:45.120 --> 00:03:47.320
<i>Will start to shine</i>

39
00:03:47.800 --> 00:03:49.880
<i>Come and see</i>

40
00:03:50.120 --> 00:03:52.160
<i>Take my hand</i>

41
00:03:52.560 --> 00:03:56.480
<i>Come with me</i>

42
00:03:57.000 --> 00:04:00.960
<i>And fly</i>

43
00:04:07.080 --> 00:04:09.280
-Morning, Stone.
-Hey, Terence.

44
00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:41.080
Come on, let's go. Flap your wings!

45
00:04:41.160 --> 00:04:44.880
Those fairies on the mainland
won't be able to fly without pixie dust!

46
00:04:44.960 --> 00:04:48.280
Terence, have you delivered
the pixie-dust rations to the scouts yet?

47
00:04:48.360 --> 00:04:50.880
Yep. Finished today's
and half of tomorrow's.

48
00:04:50.960 --> 00:04:55.760
Remember, one cup each.
No more, no less.

49
00:04:56.320 --> 00:04:58.080
I know, Fairy Gary.

50
00:04:58.400 --> 00:04:59.840
(BELL DINGS)

51
00:05:00.960 --> 00:05:02.200
(BEETLE EXCLAIMS)

52
00:05:05.120 --> 00:05:06.480
(BUZZING)

53
00:05:11.160 --> 00:05:12.440
(PANTING)

54
00:05:13.800 --> 00:05:16.960
Well, that's my cue.
I'll catch you guys later.

55
00:05:17.240 --> 00:05:19.240
And where are you off to?

56
00:05:19.760 --> 00:05:22.000
Just doing some errands and stuff.

57
00:05:22.080 --> 00:05:23.280
(EXCLAIMS)

58
00:05:23.360 --> 00:05:27.320
-Errands!
-And stuff!

59
00:05:27.400 --> 00:05:29.600
Why are you guys talking like that?

60
00:05:29.720 --> 00:05:32.000
BOTH: No reason.

61
00:05:33.720 --> 00:05:37.080
-All right.
-Say hi to Tinker Bell, would you?

62
00:05:37.160 --> 00:05:38.280
What?

63
00:05:39.440 --> 00:05:40.840
(ALL LAUGHING)

64
00:05:40.920 --> 00:05:42.320
Very funny.

65
00:05:42.520 --> 00:05:45.680
All right, you got me.
I'm gonna help Tink again.

66
00:05:47.680 --> 00:05:49.800
-Is it okay if I take this?
-FAIRY GARY: Sure.

67
00:05:49.880 --> 00:05:51.640
Thanks. See you tomorrow.

68
00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:01.520
TINKER BELL: Hammer.

69
00:06:03.040 --> 00:06:04.960
(BIRD CHIRPING)

70
00:06:13.320 --> 00:06:16.360
Thanks. Okay, try it now, Cheese.

71
00:06:16.560 --> 00:06:17.560
(SQUEAKING)

72
00:06:19.120 --> 00:06:21.840
Yeah, that's it!
Keep going. Keep going!

73
00:06:22.160 --> 00:06:25.400
Hey, Cheese.
Special delivery for Tinker Bell.

74
00:06:25.880 --> 00:06:27.080
Hi, Terence.

75
00:06:27.160 --> 00:06:30.040
Who's your best friend
that always delivers?

76
00:06:30.320 --> 00:06:31.320
Hmm.

77
00:06:31.400 --> 00:06:33.880
-Iridessa?
-Nope. Try again.

78
00:06:35.040 --> 00:06:36.880
-Fawn?
-Me!

79
00:06:36.960 --> 00:06:39.040
(CHUCKLES) Just kidding.

80
00:06:39.120 --> 00:06:42.240
So, what do you think
of the <i>Pixie Dust Express?</i>

81
00:06:42.440 --> 00:06:46.240
Wow. The guys are gonna love this
back at the depot,

82
00:06:46.880 --> 00:06:49.520
and it sure is going to help out
on the river-outpost deliveries.

83
00:06:49.600 --> 00:06:51.440
Hey, is that a stretchy thingy?

84
00:06:51.520 --> 00:06:54.640
Yeah, I thought you could use it
for your motor.

85
00:06:56.840 --> 00:06:58.200
(EXCLAIMS)

86
00:06:58.920 --> 00:07:00.920
I think it's gonna be perfect.

87
00:07:02.280 --> 00:07:03.880
(BOTH GROANING)

88
00:07:04.720 --> 00:07:05.800
TINKER BELL: Clip.

89
00:07:12.080 --> 00:07:14.600
All right, Cheese, ready to launch.

90
00:07:15.120 --> 00:07:16.320
Aah!

91
00:07:16.520 --> 00:07:17.880
(CHEERING)

92
00:07:18.840 --> 00:07:20.200
It floats!

93
00:07:20.280 --> 00:07:21.760
(ALL CHEERING)

94
00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:26.000
Okay. Are you ready
for the official test run?

95
00:07:26.440 --> 00:07:28.840
Don't worry. I'll be right next to you.

96
00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:30.480
-All set?
-Check.

97
00:07:30.640 --> 00:07:32.080
Let her rip.

98
00:07:38.400 --> 00:07:39.520
(CHUCKLING) Whoa.

99
00:07:41.080 --> 00:07:43.040
And now for hydro-drive.

100
00:07:51.720 --> 00:07:52.880
Sorry.

101
00:07:52.960 --> 00:07:54.160
(BUZZES)

102
00:07:55.360 --> 00:07:56.480
Whoa!

103
00:07:57.400 --> 00:07:58.600
Oh, no!

104
00:07:58.880 --> 00:08:00.320
(SCREAMING)

105
00:08:08.120 --> 00:08:09.600
(SCREAMING)

106
00:08:11.120 --> 00:08:12.200
Hmm.

107
00:08:13.680 --> 00:08:15.080
(SPLASH)

108
00:08:19.480 --> 00:08:20.600
Ooh!

109
00:08:23.040 --> 00:08:24.400
(GROANING)

110
00:08:31.680 --> 00:08:34.520
-Are you okay?
-Yeah. Thanks.

111
00:08:35.000 --> 00:08:35.960
(SIGHS)

112
00:08:36.040 --> 00:08:38.360
I can't believe the boat broke.

113
00:08:38.480 --> 00:08:42.000
I guess your guys
are gonna have to wait a little longer.

114
00:08:42.600 --> 00:08:43.600
I'm impressed.

115
00:08:43.680 --> 00:08:47.360
Usually when one of your inventions
doesn't work out, you overreact,

116
00:08:47.440 --> 00:08:49.560
but I must say,
you're handling this one pretty well.

117
00:08:49.640 --> 00:08:52.400
-I drove it into a tree?
-Never mind.

118
00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:53.800
(GROANS)

119
00:08:53.880 --> 00:08:55.080
Jingles!

120
00:08:55.200 --> 00:08:59.200
I made it to help you, Terence.
It should've worked.

121
00:09:01.440 --> 00:09:04.760
Come on.
Look, it just needs a little tinkering.

122
00:09:04.840 --> 00:09:07.880
Let's see.
Who do I know who's a good tinker?

123
00:09:08.400 --> 00:09:10.760
Bobble. Bobble's a good tinker.

124
00:09:10.840 --> 00:09:13.760
Or Fairy Mary,
she's got a lot of experience.

125
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:15.640
Or... Hey, what about Clank?

126
00:09:15.720 --> 00:09:16.760
(TINKER BELL GIGGLING)

127
00:09:16.840 --> 00:09:18.400
(KAZOO HUMMING)

128
00:09:19.440 --> 00:09:20.440
Uh-oh.

129
00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:24.640
-Someone's in trouble.
-Hey, I haven't done anything, lately.

130
00:09:25.120 --> 00:09:26.480
The stinkbug incident?

131
00:09:26.560 --> 00:09:27.680
(GASPS)

132
00:09:27.760 --> 00:09:29.000
Oh, no.

133
00:09:29.600 --> 00:09:32.120
Tinker Bell, Queen Clarion awaits.

134
00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:38.640
TINKER BELL: It's all
a big misunderstanding.

135
00:09:38.720 --> 00:09:42.040
I'm sure the queen wants to see me
about something completely unrelated.

136
00:09:42.120 --> 00:09:43.120
(BLOWS KAZOO)

137
00:09:43.240 --> 00:09:44.600
One moment.

138
00:09:47.800 --> 00:09:50.840
Tinker Bell is here.
She's waiting outside, my lady.

139
00:09:50.920 --> 00:09:52.600
QUEEN CLARION: Thank you, Viola.

140
00:09:52.920 --> 00:09:56.480
-Fairy Mary, are you certain?
-Whatever do you mean?

141
00:09:56.560 --> 00:10:00.520
Only that Tinker Bell,
while undoubtedly talented, also...

142
00:10:00.600 --> 00:10:03.840
-Is a hothead? Flies off the handle?
-Well, yes.

143
00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:06.520
I believe she deserves a chance,
Minister.

144
00:10:06.600 --> 00:10:09.920
After all, tinker fairies
learn from their mistakes.

145
00:10:11.960 --> 00:10:13.280
Very well.

146
00:10:13.680 --> 00:10:15.760
Agreed. Tinker Bell!

147
00:10:23.160 --> 00:10:24.720
Fairy Mary tells me she knows...

148
00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:29.000
It's not my fault, Your Highness!
Those stinkbugs were asking for it.

149
00:10:34.080 --> 00:10:37.560
-This isn't about the stinkbugs, is it?
-No.

150
00:10:37.640 --> 00:10:40.240
But we can certainly
come back to that later.

151
00:10:40.320 --> 00:10:41.400
(LAUGHING) Mary.

152
00:10:42.800 --> 00:10:45.040
You do know the Minister of Autumn.

153
00:10:45.120 --> 00:10:46.960
-My dear.
-Hi.

154
00:10:47.680 --> 00:10:50.400
Are you familiar
with the great autumn revelry?

155
00:10:50.480 --> 00:10:53.920
Well, everyone's talking about it.
They're so excited.

156
00:10:54.160 --> 00:10:56.200
Since time immemorial,

157
00:10:56.280 --> 00:10:59.480
fairies have celebrated
the end of autumn with a revelry,

158
00:10:59.560 --> 00:11:04.920
and this particular autumn
coincides with a blue harvest moon.

159
00:11:05.360 --> 00:11:09.000
A new scepter must be created
to celebrate the occasion.

160
00:11:10.000 --> 00:11:13.560
Behold, the Hall of Scepters.

161
00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:17.360
(EXCLAIMS IN AWE)

162
00:11:17.440 --> 00:11:21.080
-They're beautiful.
-Every scepter is unique.

163
00:11:21.440 --> 00:11:23.880
Some are the work of animal fairies,

164
00:11:23.960 --> 00:11:27.680
some of light fairies, or water fairies,
or garden fairies.

165
00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:31.680
This year,
it is the turn of the tinker fairies.

166
00:11:32.320 --> 00:11:35.200
And Fairy Mary has recommended you.

167
00:11:35.600 --> 00:11:36.600
(GASPS)

168
00:11:36.680 --> 00:11:41.880
-Me? But I'm... I'm...
-A very talented tinker.

169
00:11:44.440 --> 00:11:47.520
The scepter must be built
to precise dimensions.

170
00:11:47.640 --> 00:11:50.400
At the top, you will place a moonstone.

171
00:11:51.720 --> 00:11:54.040
When the blue moon is at its peak,

172
00:11:54.120 --> 00:11:59.400
its rays will pass through the gem,
creating blue pixie dust.

173
00:12:00.160 --> 00:12:03.800
QUEEN CLARION: The blue pixie dust
restores the pixie dust tree.

174
00:12:04.240 --> 00:12:08.640
Like autumn itself,
it signals rebirth and rejuvenation.

175
00:12:09.160 --> 00:12:11.240
We are relying on you.

176
00:12:12.440 --> 00:12:14.000
This way, dear.

177
00:12:15.720 --> 00:12:18.120
Here is the moonstone.

178
00:12:19.240 --> 00:12:22.720
It has been handed down
from generation to generation.

179
00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:28.080
Be careful. It is ridiculously fragile.

180
00:12:28.720 --> 00:12:32.320
Fairy Mary, I... I don't know what to say.

181
00:12:33.320 --> 00:12:36.040
-Thank you!
-Careful, Tinker Bell! Fragile!

182
00:12:36.120 --> 00:12:39.600
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

183
00:12:40.400 --> 00:12:41.520
(SIGHS)

184
00:12:41.600 --> 00:12:45.600
-Why are you counting?
-It helps to calm me down.

185
00:12:46.760 --> 00:12:51.200
Got it. Don't worry, Fairy Mary.
I'll make you proud, all of you.

186
00:12:54.880 --> 00:12:56.640
Yahoo!

187
00:13:00.200 --> 00:13:01.360
(CHIRPS)

188
00:13:01.440 --> 00:13:02.520
TERENCE: Tink!

189
00:13:04.080 --> 00:13:05.160
Tink?

190
00:13:07.280 --> 00:13:08.320
Hey!

191
00:13:13.440 --> 00:13:14.400
So?

192
00:13:14.480 --> 00:13:16.120
Terence, you're never
gonna believe this.

193
00:13:16.200 --> 00:13:19.080
Guess what happened! Go on, guess!

194
00:13:19.680 --> 00:13:20.720
Well, I...

195
00:13:20.800 --> 00:13:23.960
I have been picked
to make the new fall scepter!

196
00:13:24.480 --> 00:13:26.120
Me! Me!

197
00:13:27.200 --> 00:13:29.920
Hey, that means they...
They gave you the moonstone?

198
00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:31.640
Yeah! Want to see?

199
00:13:36.200 --> 00:13:37.240
(WHISTLES)

200
00:13:37.320 --> 00:13:40.880
Not so close. Don't breathe on it.
It's fragile.

201
00:13:41.360 --> 00:13:43.840
Yeah, I know. I know all about it.

202
00:13:43.960 --> 00:13:47.480
The blue moon only rises
in Pixie Hollow every eight years.

203
00:13:47.560 --> 00:13:50.640
The trajectory of the light beam's gotta
match the curvature of the moonstone

204
00:13:50.720 --> 00:13:52.120
at a 90-degree angle

205
00:13:52.200 --> 00:13:54.240
so the light can transmute
into pixie dust.

206
00:13:54.320 --> 00:13:57.520
Wow, Terence!
Now, how'd you know all that?

207
00:13:58.240 --> 00:14:01.760
Well, you know, every dust-keeper's
gotta study dustology.

208
00:14:01.840 --> 00:14:03.720
Hey! You know what this calls for?

209
00:14:03.800 --> 00:14:05.680
-Two cups of...
-Chamomile tea.

210
00:14:05.760 --> 00:14:08.040
-With extra honey and...
-And some milkweed whip.

211
00:14:08.160 --> 00:14:09.440
(GIGGLES)

212
00:14:09.640 --> 00:14:13.040
Hey, by the way, that new
bucket-and-pulley system you made?

213
00:14:13.160 --> 00:14:14.880
Fairy Gary loves it.

214
00:14:15.040 --> 00:14:17.680
-He's so cute.
-If you say so.

215
00:14:18.520 --> 00:14:22.760
You know what? Maybe I can help you.
You know, I'm kind of an expert on this.

216
00:14:22.880 --> 00:14:25.960
I can collect the supplies
and give you advice.

217
00:14:26.440 --> 00:14:31.000
-You will? That's... That's so sweet.
-Hey, what are friends for?

218
00:14:31.520 --> 00:14:34.160
So, what do you say?
Can I be your wingman?

219
00:14:34.240 --> 00:14:35.640
That would be great.

220
00:14:35.720 --> 00:14:38.280
-The best dust-keeper fairy.
-And the best tinker!

221
00:14:38.360 --> 00:14:40.720
This is gonna be
a revelry to remember.

222
00:14:47.640 --> 00:14:49.040
TERENCE: Knock-knock.

223
00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:51.240
(YAWNS)

224
00:14:51.720 --> 00:14:54.080
-Morning.
-Hi.

225
00:14:54.880 --> 00:14:59.920
All right, we have one full moon
until the autumn revelry. Here we go.

226
00:15:02.560 --> 00:15:05.360
Hey, Tink!
I brought you some stuff from work.

227
00:15:05.440 --> 00:15:06.560
Whoa.

228
00:15:07.240 --> 00:15:09.320
Wow, Terence, how did you...

229
00:15:09.400 --> 00:15:10.400
(SQUEAKING)

230
00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:13.880
I love this thing!

231
00:15:13.960 --> 00:15:16.560
I can tell you're gonna be a big help.

232
00:15:17.720 --> 00:15:18.800
TERENCE: Looks good.

233
00:15:18.880 --> 00:15:20.960
Now, remember,
you get the most blue pixie dust

234
00:15:21.040 --> 00:15:24.000
if you maximize the moonstone's
exposed surface area.

235
00:15:24.080 --> 00:15:25.400
Right. Got it.

236
00:15:33.120 --> 00:15:34.920
TERENCE: Knock-knickity-knock!

237
00:15:35.280 --> 00:15:36.520
(YAWNS)

238
00:15:36.920 --> 00:15:38.400
Out of bed, sleepyhead.

239
00:15:41.280 --> 00:15:43.320
You gotta keep the fire nice and hot.

240
00:15:43.400 --> 00:15:44.760
(COUGHING)

241
00:15:54.400 --> 00:15:55.800
(SCRAPING)

242
00:15:56.240 --> 00:15:58.000
(TERENCE WHISTLING)

243
00:16:02.160 --> 00:16:03.640
Excuse me, Tink.

244
00:16:03.720 --> 00:16:07.480
Yeah, you know, you should
really keep that workspace clean.

245
00:16:07.960 --> 00:16:11.360
Okay, let me just...
Let me get that one right there.

246
00:16:15.200 --> 00:16:16.880
Just one more. Thank you.

247
00:16:16.960 --> 00:16:18.960
-Whoa!
-One, two, three...

248
00:16:19.040 --> 00:16:20.160
-Why are you counting?
