Allow me to demonstrate.

275
00:18:35.760 --> 00:18:40.040
Iridessa and Rosetta will mix
light crystals with flower pigment.

276
00:18:40.400 --> 00:18:43.720
The mixture will go into the launcher,
like so.

277
00:18:44.120 --> 00:18:46.880
Then I tighten the spring, like so.

278
00:18:47.120 --> 00:18:49.720
-Oh, dear. Clank...
-Then you throw the trigger...

279
00:18:49.800 --> 00:18:51.920
-Yes, Clank...
-...and the fireworks shoot into the air!

280
00:18:52.000 --> 00:18:53.600
-Clank!
-Like so!

281
00:18:53.680 --> 00:18:55.040
(SCREAMING)

282
00:18:57.880 --> 00:18:59.920
Clanky, that's brilliant!

283
00:19:00.480 --> 00:19:04.480
Hey, Bobble. Listen, do you know
where I can find a sharp thingy?

284
00:19:04.840 --> 00:19:07.360
-A sharp thingy?
-How about a stick?

285
00:19:08.760 --> 00:19:14.000
-No, a sharp thingy-majigy.
-A stick can be pretty sharp!

286
00:19:14.640 --> 00:19:17.480
No, I need something sharper
to help Tink.

287
00:19:18.160 --> 00:19:19.240
CLANK: For Tink!

288
00:19:19.320 --> 00:19:23.360
-Clank, don't sneak up on me like that.
-Did you try the cove?

289
00:19:24.080 --> 00:19:26.960
Of course! That's where
all the lost things wash up.

290
00:19:27.040 --> 00:19:31.160
-Thanks, Bobble. Thanks, Clank.
-Our pleasure. So long, Terence!

291
00:19:33.200 --> 00:19:35.360
I'm getting a little dizzy.

292
00:19:35.880 --> 00:19:37.080
Uh-oh.

293
00:19:42.800 --> 00:19:44.000
(BLOWS)

294
00:19:47.240 --> 00:19:48.480
Perfect.

295
00:19:49.120 --> 00:19:53.680
And now for the finishing touch,
a spattering of silver shavings.

296
00:19:57.000 --> 00:20:00.080
Steady. I can't wait till she sees this.

297
00:20:03.880 --> 00:20:04.960
Oh!

298
00:20:16.080 --> 00:20:17.640
There. Perfect.

299
00:20:18.840 --> 00:20:21.040
-Finally.
-TERENCE: Hey, Tink! I'm back!

300
00:20:21.840 --> 00:20:23.040
(SIGHS)

301
00:20:26.840 --> 00:20:29.480
-What is this?
-It's your sharp thingy.

302
00:20:29.600 --> 00:20:31.680
My... That's not...

303
00:20:32.240 --> 00:20:34.880
One, two, three, four...

304
00:20:35.800 --> 00:20:39.560
Terence, this is not sharp.
This is round.

305
00:20:39.920 --> 00:20:42.880
It is, in fact, the exact opposite of sharp.

306
00:20:43.320 --> 00:20:47.400
-Really, look, if you look inside, it's...
-I need to work, okay?

307
00:20:47.840 --> 00:20:51.000
Now, would you please
get this thing out of here?

308
00:21:00.080 --> 00:21:01.440
My scepter!

309
00:21:04.880 --> 00:21:07.680
Tink, I'm so sorry. I...

310
00:21:08.000 --> 00:21:11.280
-Out, Terence! Just go!
-What?

311
00:21:11.800 --> 00:21:15.400
You brought this stupid thing here.
You broke the scepter.

312
00:21:15.480 --> 00:21:17.760
-This is your fault!
-Tink, I...

313
00:21:18.080 --> 00:21:22.600
-I was just trying to be a good friend. I...
-Go away! Just leave me alone!

314
00:21:24.200 --> 00:21:27.440
Fine! Last time I try to help you.

315
00:21:44.800 --> 00:21:46.120
(SCREAMS)

316
00:21:46.560 --> 00:21:48.160
Ow! Ow! Ouch! Ouch! Ouch!

317
00:21:52.800 --> 00:21:53.840
No.

318
00:22:12.680 --> 00:22:18.200
Kept her workspace clean,
brought her food, stoked the fire!

319
00:22:18.400 --> 00:22:21.360
"Find a sharp thingy."
Searched high and low,

320
00:22:23.080 --> 00:22:24.720
and she didn't even say thank you!

321
00:22:24.800 --> 00:22:26.160
(CROAKING)

322
00:22:29.560 --> 00:22:30.680
Whoa.

323
00:22:32.600 --> 00:22:33.960
(GROANING)

324
00:22:39.040 --> 00:22:42.520
I know some rock fairies
that are gonna be pretty upset.

325
00:22:43.400 --> 00:22:45.760
What? There are no rock fairies.

326
00:22:45.840 --> 00:22:46.840
(CHUCKLES)

327
00:22:46.960 --> 00:22:49.240
You never know. There might be.

328
00:22:50.440 --> 00:22:51.920
Are you okay?

329
00:22:52.360 --> 00:22:54.920
Yeah, I'm great! Why do you ask?

330
00:22:57.240 --> 00:23:00.880
I'm... No. I'm sorry.
I... I had a fight with Tink.

331
00:23:01.880 --> 00:23:03.360
What happened?

332
00:23:03.720 --> 00:23:08.120
There was just an accident,
and she just... She just exploded. I...

333
00:23:08.640 --> 00:23:10.080
She exploded?

334
00:23:10.560 --> 00:23:12.280
No, no, I don't mean like that.

335
00:23:12.360 --> 00:23:14.760
I mean, she just yelled at me,
you know? And...

336
00:23:14.840 --> 00:23:15.920
Oh!

337
00:23:16.000 --> 00:23:17.120
(LAUGHING)

338
00:23:17.560 --> 00:23:19.240
Did she turn red?

339
00:23:19.320 --> 00:23:22.040
Well, of course she turned red!
It's Tink!

340
00:23:22.120 --> 00:23:24.600
Just give her a chance to cool off.

341
00:23:24.920 --> 00:23:26.120
(SIGHS)

342
00:23:26.280 --> 00:23:28.400
Yeah, you're probably right.

343
00:23:47.440 --> 00:23:48.560
(GASPS)

344
00:23:49.920 --> 00:23:51.200
(SIGHS)

345
00:23:51.960 --> 00:23:54.280
-CLANK: Hello, Tink!
-Clank! Bobble!

346
00:23:54.560 --> 00:23:57.480
Came to see if you wanted to join us
for fairytale theater.

347
00:23:57.560 --> 00:23:59.640
BOBBLE: We figure you could use
a real break.

348
00:23:59.720 --> 00:24:02.440
Break? Nothing's broken!
What do you mean?

349
00:24:02.520 --> 00:24:04.160
What do you know?

350
00:24:04.400 --> 00:24:06.040
Sorry, fellas. Busy.

351
00:24:06.120 --> 00:24:08.880
You know, the revelry,
fall scepter, whatnot.

352
00:24:08.960 --> 00:24:11.320
I can't wait to see that scepter!

353
00:24:12.280 --> 00:24:15.600
-Try.
-Is it as beautiful as I imagine?

354
00:24:15.880 --> 00:24:17.000
Uh...

355
00:24:17.120 --> 00:24:20.120
-No.
-Terence told us it's amazing.

356
00:24:20.680 --> 00:24:22.800
We're so proud of you.

357
00:24:24.600 --> 00:24:28.400
-Look, guys, I really don't have time.
-Well, not to worry, Tink.

358
00:24:28.480 --> 00:24:31.040
We'll tell Fairy Mary
you couldn't make it.

359
00:24:31.120 --> 00:24:33.040
-Fairy Mary?
-Well, sure!

360
00:24:33.120 --> 00:24:36.320
You know her.
She never misses fairytale theater.

361
00:24:37.160 --> 00:24:38.400
Bye-bye!

362
00:24:43.200 --> 00:24:45.320
Clank! Bobble! Wait for me!

363
00:24:52.640 --> 00:24:53.680
(CLEARS THROAT)

364
00:24:53.760 --> 00:24:55.080
Fairy Mary, I...

365
00:24:55.160 --> 00:24:58.440
Tinker Bell!
I wasn't expecting to see you tonight.

366
00:24:58.720 --> 00:25:00.960
Have you finished the scepter?

367
00:25:01.120 --> 00:25:03.600
Well, not exactly.

368
00:25:03.920 --> 00:25:07.360
I... I was wondering...
I mean, I have to ask you...

369
00:25:07.680 --> 00:25:09.240
Yes?

370
00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:11.280
It's about the moonstone.

371
00:25:11.360 --> 00:25:15.400
What happened to it? You didn't lose it.
Tell me you didn't lose it!

372
00:25:15.480 --> 00:25:18.080
-I didn't lose it.
-Good.

373
00:25:18.200 --> 00:25:22.120
But I was thinking, if using one
moonstone creates blue pixie dust,

374
00:25:22.200 --> 00:25:24.600
using two would create even more.

375
00:25:25.200 --> 00:25:26.680
Do you have another moonstone?

376
00:25:26.760 --> 00:25:31.000
That moonstone is the only one found
in the last 100 years.

377
00:25:31.360 --> 00:25:33.160
And thank goodness we found it.

378
00:25:33.240 --> 00:25:36.760
Without the blue dust,
the pixie dust tree would grow weak,

379
00:25:36.840 --> 00:25:40.040
and things would be pretty tough
around here, believe you me.

380
00:25:40.120 --> 00:25:41.120
(THUD)

381
00:25:41.200 --> 00:25:42.200
(GASPS)

382
00:25:42.280 --> 00:25:45.320
Are you okay? You look sort of pale.

383
00:25:46.160 --> 00:25:49.720
-Wait. I know what's going on.
-You do?

384
00:25:49.960 --> 00:25:54.720
You've been working too hard.
What you need is a little theater.

385
00:25:55.200 --> 00:25:59.120
Knowing you, you'd probably redo
the whole scepter if you could.

386
00:25:59.280 --> 00:26:02.160
-Is that an option?
-(CHUCKLING) Tinker Bell!

387
00:26:02.240 --> 00:26:05.080
(CHIME TINKLING)

388
00:26:10.760 --> 00:26:12.800
(ORCHESTRA PLAYING SOFT MUSIC)

389
00:26:31.600 --> 00:26:33.040
How exciting!

390
00:26:42.280 --> 00:26:44.560
-(SINGING) <i>Hush, fairies! Hush, fairies!</i>
-(SINGING) <i>Hush, fairies! Hush, fairies!</i>

