00:26:44.640 --> 00:26:51.080
<i>-'Tis the moment for ancient fairy lore</i>
<i>-'Tis the moment for ancient fairy lore</i>

392
00:26:52.000 --> 00:26:54.000
Tinker Bell, do you mind?

393
00:26:54.680 --> 00:26:56.000
(SNIFFING)

394
00:26:56.080 --> 00:26:57.960
Sorry. Skunk training.

395
00:26:58.520 --> 00:27:00.880
<i>-Hush, fairies! Hush!</i>
<i>-Hush, fairies! Hush!</i>

396
00:27:00.960 --> 00:27:06.880
<i>-For a fairytale of yore!</i>
<i>-For a fairytale of yore!</i>

397
00:27:12.840 --> 00:27:14.640
'Twas a distant fall

398
00:27:14.960 --> 00:27:17.680
when a pirate ship
arrived in Neverland.

399
00:27:18.240 --> 00:27:21.040
The dreaded pirates swarmed ashore,

400
00:27:22.800 --> 00:27:26.160
seeking the greatest
and most elusive prize of all.

401
00:27:26.760 --> 00:27:28.000
A fairy.

402
00:27:29.280 --> 00:27:31.240
Pirates give me the willies!

403
00:27:31.320 --> 00:27:35.280
Far and wide, the pirates searched
until they found a fairy.

404
00:27:36.000 --> 00:27:38.280
They chased her, captured her

405
00:27:38.360 --> 00:27:41.960
and forced her to lead them
to the most magical treasure,

406
00:27:42.200 --> 00:27:45.040
the enchanted Mirror of Incanta.

407
00:27:50.520 --> 00:27:53.800
Forged by fairy magic in ages past,

408
00:27:54.240 --> 00:27:57.600
the mirror had the power
to grant three wishes,

409
00:27:58.240 --> 00:28:00.560
anything precious to your heart.

410
00:28:01.640 --> 00:28:04.600
-Fairy Mary, is this true?
-Every word.

411
00:28:05.280 --> 00:28:07.520
The pirates used two wishes,

412
00:28:08.160 --> 00:28:10.960
but before they could use
the third wish,

413
00:28:11.760 --> 00:28:16.120
the ship was wrecked
on an island north of Neverland.

414
00:28:18.000 --> 00:28:22.480
The Mirror of Incanta,
with its last remaining wish,

415
00:28:23.360 --> 00:28:26.240
was lost forever.

416
00:28:28.040 --> 00:28:29.400
(EXCLAIMS)

417
00:28:29.520 --> 00:28:36.200
Yet it is said that the clues to find it
are hidden in this ancient chant.

418
00:28:37.400 --> 00:28:40.640
"Journey due north past Neverland

419
00:28:41.120 --> 00:28:45.000
"Till a faraway island is close at hand

420
00:28:45.640 --> 00:28:49.560
(SINGING)<i> "When you're alone</i>
<i>But not alone</i>

421
00:28:49.760 --> 00:28:56.080
<i>"You will find help</i>
<i>And an arch of stone"</i>

422
00:28:57.000 --> 00:28:58.480
Arch of stone.

423
00:29:00.960 --> 00:29:04.320
"There's one way across
the isle's north ridge

424
00:29:04.560 --> 00:29:08.280
"But a price must be paid
at the old troll bridge"

425
00:29:09.160 --> 00:29:10.160
What did she say?

426
00:29:10.240 --> 00:29:12.360
I think she said something
about a toll bridge.

427
00:29:12.480 --> 00:29:13.840
-Toll bridge?
-Yeah.

428
00:29:13.920 --> 00:29:16.520
-But I don't know how much it costs.
-Oh?

429
00:29:17.800 --> 00:29:20.720
"At journey's end
You shall walk the plank

430
00:29:21.160 --> 00:29:25.640
"Of the ship that sunk
But never sank"

431
00:29:26.840 --> 00:29:30.760
(SINGING) <i>"And in the hold</i>
<i>Amidst gems and gold</i>

432
00:29:30.840 --> 00:29:37.800
<i>"A wish come true</i>
<i>Awaits, we're told</i>

433
00:29:40.800 --> 00:29:42.280
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

434
00:29:47.440 --> 00:29:52.040
<i>"But beware and be warned</i>
<i>There's a trick to this clue</i>

435
00:29:52.280 --> 00:29:57.360
<i>"Wish only goodwill</i>
<i>Or no good will come you</i>

436
00:29:57.480 --> 00:30:00.000
<i>"For the treasure you seek</i>

437
00:30:00.560 --> 00:30:07.520
<i>"You may yet come to rue!"</i>

438
00:30:12.920 --> 00:30:15.080
AUDIENCE: Bravo! Bravo!

439
00:30:16.200 --> 00:30:19.520
Bravo! Bravo!

440
00:30:20.640 --> 00:30:23.880
"Faraway island is close at hand

441
00:30:29.200 --> 00:30:31.680
"Due north past Neverland"

442
00:30:37.240 --> 00:30:39.240
Let's see. Mouse cheese.

443
00:30:41.880 --> 00:30:42.920
Um...

444
00:30:43.000 --> 00:30:44.520
Pan. Chart.

445
00:30:46.520 --> 00:30:48.000
Extra clothes.

446
00:30:51.400 --> 00:30:53.600
This one's not for traveling.

447
00:30:54.400 --> 00:30:56.640
How am I gonna carry all this?

448
00:30:59.480 --> 00:31:00.520
Not enough.

449
00:31:01.840 --> 00:31:04.680
-There you go. One cup, dear.
-Thank you.

450
00:31:05.600 --> 00:31:07.320
Fairy Gary. Hi.

451
00:31:07.680 --> 00:31:10.360
Hello, Tink. What brings you here?

452
00:31:10.640 --> 00:31:13.960
I see that bucket-and-pulley system
l rigged for you is working out.

453
00:31:14.040 --> 00:31:17.120
You know, Fairy Gary,
you really run a tight ship.

454
00:31:17.200 --> 00:31:21.360
I know it sounds like I'm just saying it,
but you really do. Really.

455
00:31:21.560 --> 00:31:22.960
That's very sweet, dear.

456
00:31:23.040 --> 00:31:27.520
Anyway, I was wondering,
can I have some extra pixie dust?

457
00:31:27.600 --> 00:31:28.960
(LAUGHING)

458
00:31:30.040 --> 00:31:31.120
Pardon?

459
00:31:31.240 --> 00:31:34.560
Come on, Fairy Gary. Please?
Just a smidge?

460
00:31:35.200 --> 00:31:38.720
Now, Tinker Bell, you know the rules,

461
00:31:38.880 --> 00:31:43.080
and it says here
you already got your ration.

462
00:31:44.520 --> 00:31:45.720
(GROANS)

463
00:31:50.640 --> 00:31:52.320
Iridessa! Rosetta!

464
00:31:52.960 --> 00:31:55.480
-What do you think?
-Lend you some of our dust?

465
00:31:55.600 --> 00:31:58.240
Tinker Bell,
we need every bit of it on the mainland.

466
00:31:58.320 --> 00:32:01.720
Sweetie, it takes a lot of flying
to bring in autumn.

467
00:32:02.560 --> 00:32:03.920
Sorry, Tink.

468
00:32:06.200 --> 00:32:08.400
Say, you know who can help.

469
00:32:13.280 --> 00:32:16.920
Raffaela, Renato, Redina, Rina...

470
00:32:17.640 --> 00:32:19.200
-Hi, Cheese!
-Hey, Terence!

471
00:32:19.280 --> 00:32:20.760
Morning, Fawn!

472
00:32:21.160 --> 00:32:23.960
-Rina, Rhoda, Rosetta...
-Terence.

473
00:32:25.280 --> 00:32:27.120
-Tink?
-Hi.

474
00:32:28.440 --> 00:32:31.600
Surprised to see you.
How's the scepter?

475
00:32:32.320 --> 00:32:34.280
I'm working on it.

476
00:32:34.880 --> 00:32:38.600
Look, Terence, things happened,
mistakes were made,

477
00:32:38.680 --> 00:32:42.120
and now there's something
I need to talk to you about.

478
00:32:43.440 --> 00:32:45.640
I need some extra pixie dust.

479
00:32:47.480 --> 00:32:50.640
You need more pixie dust?
That's why you're here?

480
00:32:50.800 --> 00:32:51.880
Yeah.

481
00:32:51.960 --> 00:32:55.760
It's not exactly what I was expecting.
Why do you need more dust?

482
00:32:55.840 --> 00:32:58.600
I... I can't tell you.

483
00:32:59.280 --> 00:33:00.680
You can't tell me?

484
00:33:00.760 --> 00:33:04.040
You need more pixie dust,
and you can't tell me why?

485
00:33:04.120 --> 00:33:06.800
A true friend
wouldn't need to know why.

486
00:33:07.040 --> 00:33:10.000
A true friend wouldn't ask me
to break the rules!

487
00:33:10.080 --> 00:33:12.920
Well, then,
I guess we're not true friends!

488
00:33:16.200 --> 00:33:17.440
No, I...

489
00:33:19.600 --> 00:33:21.240
I guess we're not.

490
00:33:21.720 --> 00:33:23.520
I'm on my own, then.

491
00:33:24.720 --> 00:33:26.000
(CRYING)

492
00:34:02.120 --> 00:34:03.360
(CAWING)

493
00:34:04.040 --> 00:34:05.040
What?

494
00:34:05.280 --> 00:34:06.720
(EXCLAIMING)

495
00:34:44.800 --> 00:34:46.160
(GROANING)

496
00:35:43.800 --> 00:35:46.800
So long, Pixie Hollow. I'll be back soon.

497
00:36:09.200 --> 00:36:12.520
I just need to angle the moon
with the horizon.

498
00:36:28.800 --> 00:36:30.160
(EXCLAIMS)

499
00:36:34.040 --> 00:36:35.160
Huh?

500
00:36:36.400 --> 00:36:37.400
(GASPS)

501
00:36:38.600 --> 00:36:39.600
(SCREAMS)

502
00:37:13.160 --> 00:37:14.160
(EXHALES)

503
00:37:14.240 --> 00:37:15.720
I'm starving.

504
00:37:19.960 --> 00:37:21.760
My boysenberry rolls!

505
00:37:29.920 --> 00:37:31.320
(SQUEAKING)

506
00:37:36.920 --> 00:37:38.160
(BURPS)

507
00:37:42.080 --> 00:37:45.080
My mouse cheese!
My pumpernickel muffin!

508
00:37:47.000 --> 00:37:49.800
Out. Out. Shoo. Go find your friends.

509
00:37:57.680 --> 00:37:58.680
(SQUEAKS)

510
00:37:59.600 --> 00:38:01.280
Stop following me.

511
00:38:01.680 --> 00:38:03.480
I'm on a very important mission.

512
00:38:03.560 --> 00:38:06.880
I have two days to find the magic mirror
and wish the moonstone back.

513
00:38:06.960 --> 00:38:07.920
(SQUEAKS)

514
00:38:08.000 --> 00:38:09.520
No, I don't need any help.

515
00:38:09.600 --> 00:38:10.560
(SQUEAKS)

516
00:38:10.680 --> 00:38:13.360
Yes, I am sure. Okay. Now, let's see.

517
00:38:16.040 --> 00:38:17.280
(GRUNTS)

518
00:38:17.440 --> 00:38:20.600
Hey, look! Look, little guy. Fetch!

519
00:38:22.160 --> 00:38:23.200
(EXCLAIMS)

520
00:38:23.280 --> 00:38:25.960
Will you please get out of here?

521
00:38:39.720 --> 00:38:41.400
That does it. Out!

522
00:39:21.360 --> 00:39:22.360
(GASPS)

523
00:39:28.800 --> 00:39:31.360
All right. You can stay.

524
00:39:32.720 --> 00:39:38.280
For now. Just do me a favor,
if you could stay right here.

525
00:39:40.160 --> 00:39:43.480
If my bearings are accurate,
we should see land soon.

526
00:39:44.720 --> 00:39:47.520
I'm Tinker Bell. What's your name?

527
00:39:47.600 --> 00:39:48.640
(SQUEAKS)

528
00:39:48.720 --> 00:39:50.720
Okay. Blinky?

529
00:39:51.800 --> 00:39:55.720
Flicker? Flash? Beam? Flare?

530
00:39:56.560 --> 00:39:59.160
Well, how in the blazing bellows
am I supposed to guess your name

531
00:39:59.240 --> 00:40:00.240
if you keep...

532
00:40:00.320 --> 00:40:01.320
(SQUEAKS)

533
00:40:02.560 --> 00:40:04.320
Your name's Bellows?

534
00:40:04.720 --> 00:40:05.960
Oh, Blaze.

535
00:40:08.000 --> 00:40:10.800
Kind of a tough-guy name.
You a tough guy?

536
00:40:11.800 --> 00:40:13.120
(LAUGHING)

537
00:40:13.200 --> 00:40:15.240
Okay. Don't hurt yourself.

538
00:40:16.560 --> 00:40:19.120
IRIDESSA: That's it, Cheese.
Keep them coming.

539
00:40:19.440 --> 00:40:20.600
Next.

540
00:40:21.920 --> 00:40:23.280
Okay. Next.

541
00:40:23.880 --> 00:40:26.440
Iridessa,
how are those lanterns coming?

542
00:40:26.520 --> 00:40:30.640
Almost done, Fairy Mary. Whoa!
Good shot, Cheese.

543
00:40:31.200 --> 00:40:33.840
Next, I'll get Rosetta some light crystals
for the fireworks.

544
00:40:33.920 --> 00:40:38.000
I can't wait to mix them up
with my begonias, gardenias and...

545
00:40:40.240 --> 00:40:42.600
-Forget-me-nots.
-Forget-me-nots.

546
00:40:42.760 --> 00:40:44.760
I keep forgetting those.

547
00:40:45.440 --> 00:40:49.240
Fawn, show me how that
21-butterfly salute is coming along.

548
00:40:49.320 --> 00:40:52.880
All right, fellas, when I blow the whistle,
you guys go.

549
00:40:53.000 --> 00:40:54.000
(EXCLAIMING IN AGREEMENT)

550
00:40:54.080 --> 00:40:56.040
On your mark, get set...

551
00:40:56.120 --> 00:40:57.280
(BUTTERFLIES EXCLAIMING)

552
00:40:57.360 --> 00:40:58.640
(SIGHS)

553
00:40:58.880 --> 00:41:00.240
(WHISTLES)

554
00:41:00.680 --> 00:41:02.560
One down and 20 to go.

555
00:41:03.320 --> 00:41:07.120
Keep at it, sweetie.
Silvermist, what are you working on?

556
00:41:07.200 --> 00:41:09.440
Pollywog bubbles. Okay, guys.

557
00:41:14.800 --> 00:41:16.040
Ooh!

558
00:41:16.160 --> 00:41:17.440
(FAIRY MARY CHUCKLES)

559
00:41:18.240 --> 00:41:20.640
-There you go.
-Nicely done, dear.

560
00:41:20.840 --> 00:41:22.000
Next.

561
00:41:22.680 --> 00:41:25.240
Fireworks. Is it ready yet?

562
00:41:25.320 --> 00:41:26.640
-Yes!
-Let her rip!

563
00:41:26.720 --> 00:41:28.520
-Right, Bobble.
-Dear.

564
00:41:28.960 --> 00:41:30.320
(SCREAMING)

565
00:41:32.640 --> 00:41:33.920
BOBBLE: I'm okay.

566
00:41:34.120 --> 00:41:35.800
(SCREAMING)

567
00:41:37.000 --> 00:41:38.040
(EXCLAIMS)

568
00:41:38.120 --> 00:41:39.480
BOBBLE: Still okay.

569
00:41:40.600 --> 00:41:41.840
Honestly.

570
00:41:54.720 --> 00:41:56.240
One, two.

571
00:41:58.840 --> 00:42:02.400
I don't understand, Blaze.
We should've seen land by now.

572
00:42:04.520 --> 00:42:07.840
You go ahead and get some rest.
I'll take first watch.

573
00:42:37.400 --> 00:42:41.640
Whoa! I'm awake, I'm awake, I'm...
In a tree?

574
00:42:42.760 --> 00:42:44.960
This must be the lost island.

575
00:42:46.320 --> 00:42:49.160
There it is.
The stone arch from the story!

576
00:42:49.560 --> 00:42:52.120
You stay here and guard the balloon.

577
00:42:53.760 --> 00:42:55.520
I'll be right back.

578
00:43:13.440 --> 00:43:14.480
Oh!

579
00:43:14.640 --> 00:43:16.000
Oh, no.

580
00:43:16.080 --> 00:43:20.360
This is supposed to be a rock arch,
not a twisty, branchy, tree arch.

581
00:43:33.720 --> 00:43:35.040
(SQUEAKING)

582
00:43:35.520 --> 00:43:36.800
Not now.

583
00:43:39.440 --> 00:43:41.000
(SQUEAKING)

584
00:43:42.400 --> 00:43:44.400
What has gotten into you?

585
00:43:46.680 --> 00:43:48.800
Blaze, where's the balloon?

586
00:43:49.120 --> 00:43:50.400
(SQUEAKING)

587
00:43:50.560 --> 00:43:51.880
It's gone?

588
00:43:52.080 --> 00:43:54.960
My compass, my supplies,
my pixie dust.

589
00:43:55.440 --> 00:43:58.360
I left you in charge.
Why didn't you warn me?

590
00:44:00.480 --> 00:44:02.160
Well, I... You...

591
00:44:02.800 --> 00:44:07.080
Okay, okay. We'll get back to that later.
We gotta find that balloon.

592
00:44:14.200 --> 00:44:15.560
(GROANING)

593
00:44:23.680 --> 00:44:24.720
(BLAZE SHRIEKS)

594
00:44:24.800 --> 00:44:25.960
Blaze!

595
00:44:35.760 --> 00:44:36.840
TERENCE: Tink?

596
00:44:40.680 --> 00:44:45.800
-I'm so sorry...
-Terence. Terence. How did you...

597
00:44:45.880 --> 00:44:49.440
You brought this stupid thing here.
You broke the scepter.

598
00:44:49.520 --> 00:44:51.720
-This is your fault!
-Tink, I...

599
00:44:51.800 --> 00:44:54.040
I was just trying to be a good friend. I...

600
00:44:54.120 --> 00:44:55.840
Just leave me alone!

601
00:44:58.240 --> 00:45:00.720
Fine! Last time I try to help you.

602
00:45:05.040 --> 00:45:09.080
No. Terence, come back. Terence.

603
00:45:10.480 --> 00:45:11.720
Terence.

604
00:45:22.080 --> 00:45:23.880
Blaze, where are you?

605
00:45:25.480 --> 00:45:26.640
Blaze!

606
00:45:34.160 --> 00:45:39.680
I lost my balloon. I lost my pixie dust.
I'm starving.

607
00:45:41.080 --> 00:45:42.720
What have I done?

608
00:46:16.960 --> 00:46:18.320
(BOTH EXCLAIM)

609
00:46:33.880 --> 00:46:34.960
(CHUCKLES)

610
00:46:49.200 --> 00:46:53.160
Wow, that hit the spot.
Thank you so much.

611
00:46:57.440 --> 00:46:59.040
Hey, we're lost.

612
00:46:59.640 --> 00:47:03.520
By any chance, have you seen
a stone arch around here?

613
00:47:20.520 --> 00:47:21.840
(GROANING)

614
00:47:24.080 --> 00:47:27.880
I'm out of dust.
Looks like I'll be walking from here.

615
00:47:37.240 --> 00:47:38.600
My compass!

616
00:47:40.680 --> 00:47:41.840
(GROANING)

617
00:47:42.400 --> 00:47:43.520
Ouch!

618
00:47:44.160 --> 00:47:46.040
That is a sharp thingy.

619
00:47:46.800 --> 00:47:48.040
Terence.

620
00:47:59.640 --> 00:48:04.040
The stone arch. Blaze, hey, we made it!
We're here!

621
00:48:07.880 --> 00:48:09.560
Thank you so much.

622
00:48:10.640 --> 00:48:14.320
Thank you all so much. Bye, now. Bye!

623
00:48:16.400 --> 00:48:19.600
Great to have friends
that will help you out, huh?

624
00:48:23.160 --> 00:48:24.400
(SIGHS)

625
00:48:26.240 --> 00:48:28.480
I know Tink is my best friend.

626
00:48:29.120 --> 00:48:31.520
We should just forgive each other.

627
00:48:31.600 --> 00:48:35.120
Someone just needs
to take the first step.

628
00:48:35.720 --> 00:48:36.760
MALE VOICE: Who?

629
00:48:37.400 --> 00:48:40.040
Yeah, well, I think it should be Tink.

630
00:48:40.240 --> 00:48:42.560
-Who?
-Tink.

631
00:48:43.040 --> 00:48:45.680
She blamed me
for breaking the scepter.

632
00:48:46.640 --> 00:48:49.160
-Who?
-Tink!

633
00:48:49.720 --> 00:48:51.200
I know she's under a lot of pressure,

634
00:48:51.320 --> 00:48:54.160
but she shouldn't
have treated me that way.

635
00:48:54.640 --> 00:48:56.440
She should apologize.

636
00:48:57.040 --> 00:48:58.160
Who?

637
00:49:03.960 --> 00:49:04.960
Me.

638
00:49:06.680 --> 00:49:08.080
Thank you so much, Mr. Owl.

639
00:49:08.160 --> 00:49:11.960
You know what? You are truly
the wisest of all the creatures.

640
00:49:16.400 --> 00:49:19.640
The fellows are making fun
of my kilt again.

641
00:49:20.760 --> 00:49:23.120
-Who?
-The guys at the depot!

642
00:49:23.360 --> 00:49:25.600
They keep calling it a skirt.

643
00:49:33.320 --> 00:49:35.800
Hey, Tink, it's me.

644
00:49:36.760 --> 00:49:41.560
Look, I know you're mad at me, okay,
but there's something I need to tell you.

645
00:49:43.040 --> 00:49:44.160
Tink?

646
00:49:50.400 --> 00:49:51.840
Anyone home?

647
00:49:56.840 --> 00:49:58.320
The moonstone.

648
00:50:03.000 --> 00:50:04.120
What?

649
00:50:15.400 --> 00:50:16.400
(GRUNTS)

650
00:50:17.680 --> 00:50:21.400
It's our last day, Blaze.
We gotta find that shipwreck soon.

651
00:50:38.760 --> 00:50:42.000
BOTH: None shall pass
the secret troll bridge.

652
00:50:42.240 --> 00:50:45.760
Troll bridge?
I thought it was "toll bridge."

653
00:50:46.200 --> 00:50:49.640
-Look, fellas, I don't want any trouble.
-We are guardians of the secret...

654
00:50:49.720 --> 00:50:52.680
-Hey, hey, hey! Hey!
-What?

655
00:50:52.760 --> 00:50:55.600
It's my turn to give
the ominous warning, blockhead.

656
00:50:55.680 --> 00:50:56.960
-Is not.
-Is too.

657
00:50:57.040 --> 00:51:01.640
-Is not! Not! Not! Not! Not! Not!
-Is too! Is too! Too! Too! Too! Too! Too!

658
00:51:01.720 --> 00:51:03.520
You did it last time.

659
00:51:03.720 --> 00:51:06.560
That was over 300 years ago!

660
00:51:07.320 --> 00:51:08.560
(GROWLS)

661
00:51:09.000 --> 00:51:10.240
Go ahead.

662
00:51:11.080 --> 00:51:14.600
We are guardians of the secret bridge.

663
00:51:14.920 --> 00:51:19.080
Beat it before we grind your bones
to make our bed.

664
00:51:20.800 --> 00:51:22.400
-Bread.
-What?

665
00:51:23.360 --> 00:51:29.080
The expression is, "Grind your bones
to make our bread," not "bed."

666
00:51:29.360 --> 00:51:31.040
Oh? Really?

667
00:51:32.640 --> 00:51:35.440
Who would want
to make bread out of bones?

668
00:51:35.840 --> 00:51:37.200
Might break a tooth.

669
00:51:37.280 --> 00:51:40.080
Well, who would want to sleep in a bed
made of bones?

670
00:51:40.240 --> 00:51:43.360
It's hard on the back. It'll put a crick
in your neck, you knucklehead.

671
00:51:43.440 --> 00:51:46.720
Ix-nay in front of the ictim-vay.

672
00:51:47.360 --> 00:51:49.000
Gravel for brains.

673
00:51:49.080 --> 00:51:50.480
TALL TROLL: Fuzz face.
SMALL TROLL: Thimble head.

674
00:51:50.560 --> 00:51:51.920
-TALL TROLL: Stinky breath.
-Googly eyes.

675
00:51:52.000 --> 00:51:53.440
-Waxy ears!
-Unibrow!

676
00:51:53.520 --> 00:51:55.520
Excuse me. I need to get through.

677
00:51:55.600 --> 00:51:58.040
BOTH: None shall pass!

678
00:51:58.280 --> 00:52:00.960
Do you have any idea
what I've been through to get here?

679
00:52:01.040 --> 00:52:02.440
I almost got attacked by bugs and bats

680
00:52:02.520 --> 00:52:04.000
and got blown all over the place
by the wind,

681
00:52:04.080 --> 00:52:06.720
and almost starved to death to find
a mirror that grants one last wish,

682
00:52:06.800 --> 00:52:07.880
which I wouldn't have even needed

683
00:52:07.960 --> 00:52:09.800
if Terence had taken his time
finding me a sharp thingy

684
00:52:09.880 --> 00:52:11.600
instead of making me
break the moonstone.

685
00:52:11.680 --> 00:52:13.720
And then he didn't even share
his pixie dust because he cares more

686
00:52:13.800 --> 00:52:15.560
about the stupid rules
than he does about me...

687
00:52:15.640 --> 00:52:17.840
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hang on, hang on, hang on.

688
00:52:17.920 --> 00:52:20.640
-Who's Terence?
-Is he a friend of yours?

689
00:52:21.240 --> 00:52:22.600
Well, yeah.

690
00:52:24.080 --> 00:52:25.960
He was my best friend.

691
00:52:27.040 --> 00:52:30.120
-You're not very nice.
-Hey, don't you judge me!

692
00:52:30.200 --> 00:52:33.480
You've been yelling at each other
since I got here.

693
00:52:33.560 --> 00:52:35.520
But he knows I don't mean it, don't you?

694
00:52:35.600 --> 00:52:37.000
You old softie.

695
00:52:37.080 --> 00:52:38.240
(CHUCKLING)

696
00:52:38.320 --> 00:52:43.360
-Like when I call you "wart face."
-Yes. Or when I call you "big nose."

697
00:52:44.480 --> 00:52:46.400
-Booger breath.
-Stinky feet.

698
00:52:46.480 --> 00:52:48.280
TALL TROLL: Weasel toes!
SMALL TROLL: Badger brain!

699
00:52:48.360 --> 00:52:52.520
-Garden gnome!
-Garden gnome?

700
00:52:53.760 --> 00:52:57.520
Oh, dear,
I don't know where that came from.

701
00:52:58.360 --> 00:53:02.600
-I crossed the line.
-(CRYING) Say the magic words. Go on.

702
00:53:06.400 --> 00:53:07.440
I'm sorry.

703
00:53:07.520 --> 00:53:10.000
-Do you mean it?
-Absolutely.

704
00:53:10.120 --> 00:53:12.080
-Do you feel it?
-Deeply.

705
00:53:13.680 --> 00:53:16.640
Well, then, I forgive you.

706
00:53:19.040 --> 00:53:21.880
-Friends?
-Friends.

707
00:53:26.240 --> 00:53:28.440
-Come here, buddy.
-Pal!

708
00:53:28.560 --> 00:53:30.560
<i>-Amigo.</i>
<i>-Compadre.</i>

709
00:53:31.360 --> 00:53:32.760
SMALL TROLL: You're the best.
TALL TROLL: No, you.

710
00:53:32.840 --> 00:53:34.640
-SMALL TROLL: No, you.
-No, you're right, I am the best.

711
00:53:34.720 --> 00:53:37.480
-So now you think you're the best?
-I know I'm the best!

712
00:53:37.560 --> 00:53:39.280
Now, don't you argue with me!

713
00:53:39.400 --> 00:53:40.480
SMALL TROLL: Well, you're ugly
and stinky.

714
00:53:40.560 --> 00:53:41.640
TALL TROLL: Really?

715
00:53:53.120 --> 00:53:55.360
Blaze, listen, it's the ocean.

716
00:54:29.800 --> 00:54:34.560
The ship that sunk but never sank.
Okay, Blaze, this is it.

717
00:54:34.880 --> 00:54:38.200
We gotta find that mirror
and fix the moonstone. Let's go.

718
00:55:05.800 --> 00:55:09.120
Why couldn't the mirror
be in a bunny-filled meadow?

719
00:55:23.880 --> 00:55:25.000
(GASPS)

720
00:55:39.680 --> 00:55:41.800
(MIMICKING ROAR)

721
00:55:45.360 --> 00:55:46.680
(LAUGHING)

722
00:55:46.840 --> 00:55:48.160
(ECHOING)

723
00:55:54.480 --> 00:55:55.640
Blaze!

724
00:56:14.040 --> 00:56:15.320
(PANTING)

725
00:56:29.120 --> 00:56:30.560
(FLUTTERING)

726
00:56:31.080 --> 00:56:33.040
Who's that? Who's there?

727
00:56:43.720 --> 00:56:44.880
(GASPS)

728
00:57:01.800 --> 00:57:03.200
(SOFTLY) Look, Blaze.

729
00:57:08.480 --> 00:57:09.840
(GROANING)

730
00:57:18.000 --> 00:57:19.040
Ah!

731
00:57:34.280 --> 00:57:36.360
What do you think? Too big?

732
00:57:37.480 --> 00:57:41.320
It's gotta be in here somewhere, Blaze.
Come on. Help me look.

733
00:58:00.800 --> 00:58:02.040
(GASPS)

734
00:58:07.280 --> 00:58:08.600
It's real.

735
00:58:20.680 --> 00:58:22.320
Okay. Deep breath.

736
00:58:23.440 --> 00:58:27.480
Clear your mind.
Only get one shot at this. Here it goes.

737
00:58:28.560 --> 00:58:31.600
I wish... I wish...

738
00:58:33.120 --> 00:58:34.520
I wish...

739
00:58:36.840 --> 00:58:39.760
Blaze, I wish you'd be quiet
for one minute!

740
00:58:40.520 --> 00:58:41.600
(GASPS)

741
00:58:45.520 --> 00:58:48.360
No, no, no, no! No!
That one didn't count!

742
00:58:48.760 --> 00:58:51.760
I take it back.
Please, please. I take it back!

743
00:58:51.840 --> 00:58:53.960
That wasn't my wish. Please!

744
00:58:54.640 --> 00:58:55.760
(SIGHS)

745
00:58:55.840 --> 00:58:58.040
Blaze, look what you've done!

746
00:58:58.400 --> 00:59:02.360
This mirror was my last chance.
